# =============================================================================
# PlanFlow - Root Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# PlanFlow uses a monorepo structure with separate environment files for each app:
#
# 📁 apps/api/.env         → Backend API server
# 📁 apps/web/.env.local   → Frontend Next.js app
#
# This file documents the overall environment setup.
# For app-specific variables, see the .env.example files in each app directory.
#
# =============================================================================
# QUICK SETUP
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy environment templates:
#
#    # API
#    cp apps/api/.env.example apps/api/.env
#
#    # Web (Next.js uses .env.local)
#    cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local
#
# 2. Configure minimum required variables:
#
#    API (apps/api/.env):
#    - DATABASE_URL or DATABASE_URL_POOLED  → Get from https://console.neon.tech
#    - JWT_SECRET                            → Generate: openssl rand -base64 48
#
#    Web (apps/web/.env.local):
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL                   → http://localhost:3001 (default)
#
# 3. Start the development servers:
#
#    pnpm dev
#
# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT FILES REFERENCE
# =============================================================================
#
# Development:
# ├── apps/api/.env.example           → API development template
# ├── apps/api/.env                   → API development config (gitignored)
# ├── apps/web/.env.example           → Web development template
# └── apps/web/.env.local             → Web development config (gitignored)
#
# Production:
# ├── apps/api/.env.production.example    → API production template
# └── apps/web/.env.production.example    → Web production template
#
# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED SERVICES
# =============================================================================
#
# Database (Required):
# - Neon PostgreSQL: https://console.neon.tech
#   - Free tier available
#   - Provides both direct and pooled connection strings
#   - Serverless-optimized
#
# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL SERVICES
# =============================================================================
#
# Email (Resend):
# - https://resend.com
# - Free tier: 3,000 emails/month
# - Used for: Password reset, notifications, team invitations
#
# Payments (LemonSqueezy):
# - https://app.lemonsqueezy.com
# - Used for: Subscription billing
# - Alternative to Stripe (works in more countries)
#
# GitHub Integration:
# - Create OAuth App: https://github.com/settings/developers
# - Used for: Link tasks to PRs/issues, auto-update task status
#
# Redis:
# - Upstash (serverless): https://upstash.com
# - Used for: Rate limiting, task locks, caching
# - Falls back to in-memory if not configured
#
# Analytics (PostHog):
# - https://app.posthog.com
# - Free tier available
# - Used for: User behavior tracking, feature flags
#
# Error Tracking (Sentry):
# - https://sentry.io
# - Free tier available
# - Used for: Error monitoring, performance tracking
#
# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# =============================================================================
#
# For production deployments on Railway, Vercel, or similar:
#
# 1. Use the .env.production.example files as reference
# 2. Set environment variables in your platform's dashboard
# 3. Ensure all REQUIRED variables are configured
# 4. Use secure, randomly generated secrets
#
# Security checklist:
# ✅ JWT_SECRET is at least 32 characters and randomly generated
# ✅ DATABASE_URL uses SSL (sslmode=require)
# ✅ CORS_ORIGINS only includes your production domains
# ✅ No secrets are prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_
#
# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================
#
# "Server won't start"
# → Check that DATABASE_URL and JWT_SECRET are set correctly
# → JWT_SECRET must be at least 32 characters
#
# "API calls failing"
# → Verify NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL points to running API server
# → Check CORS_ORIGINS includes your frontend domain
#
# "Emails not sending"
# → Verify RESEND_API_KEY is valid
# → Check that RESEND_FROM_EMAIL domain is verified in Resend
#
# "GitHub integration not working"
# → Ensure GITHUB_REDIRECT_URI matches OAuth App settings
# → Check both CLIENT_ID and CLIENT_SECRET are set
#
# =============================================================================
